

The following major international news stories from the Middle East region are scheduled to be covered or pursued by Xinhua News Agency on Monday.

-- US and Iraqi forces continued a major offensive, Operation Steel Curtain, to eradicate al-Qaida fighters in western Iraq near the Syrian border.

-- UN Secretary General Kofi Annan arrived in Cairo on a three- day visit to Egypt as part of his tour which will also take him to Saudi Arabia and Tunisia.

-- Palestinian Civil Affairs Minister Mohammed Dahlan will inspect Rafah crossing on the Egypt-Gaza border with some European officials and experts, who have been engaged as the third party in seeking the proper involvement in rerunning the cross.

